width="730"
height="365"
alt="An artist working on a canvas against a wall covered in graffiti."
/>
</picture></div></div><div
class="block-intro-text"><p>Designing an artist website can be a great creative process for the artist, as the website should reflect the style of your art. When you think of art displayed in galleries and museums, the walls are always white to properly showcase the artwork. This is a great theme to take over to designing your artist's website.</p><p>Be sure to showcase your artwork in easily accessible categories, in a way that engages your audience. It's also a great idea to have your social media handles on prominent display so customers can see new work as it's produced. Try out our <a
href="/">artist AI website builder</a> to design a great website in seconds.</p></div><div
class="mt-0 mt-md-2 entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="block-wrapper"><div
class="block block-heads-up"><div
class="heads-up-title-wrapper">
