class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="rose-hewartson" class="entry-website-title">Rose Hewartson</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-rose-hewartson-20240611-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-rose-hewartson-20240611-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-rose-hewartson-20240611-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Rose Hewartson"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.rosehewartson.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.rosehewartson.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Brisbane, Queensland, Australia</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Rose Hewartson is an artist based in Brisbane who specializes in country themes with a contemporary, urban twist. The site's off-white background and minimal use of text highlight the colorful charm of this artist's paintings, while customer reviews enhance the credibility of the site.</p><p>The site includes an introduction to the artist and her style of work, and offers visitors the option to view works available for purchase, opportunities to learn from the artist, or book an appointment with the artist. The use of different media styles, including images, videos, and GIFs, enhances user engagement.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is visually engaging and offers a lot of features that visitors to the site would be looking for, including an artist's bio, commission appointments, and a gallery of work with pricing information.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is only semi-compliant with assistive technologies, and one of the pages does not display the menu. WAVE reports some empty link, empty heading, and contrast errors. The site lacks a resume of past and future exhibitions and events.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-rose-hewartson-20240611-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-rose-hewartson-20240611-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop site makes great use of the responsive design and visual impact to draw in potential customers. Some text blocks offer poor contrast to the background color, but the site itself performs well, having a performance score of 93/100 on Google's PageSpeed Insights report. With a menu at the top and bottom of each page and prominent social media links, visitors can easily navigate the desktop site.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-rosehewartson-20240522-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-rosehewartson-20240522-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile site is well-optimized for the smaller screen, with plenty of white space maintaining legibility and easy navigation. The hamburger menu maintains the easy navigation and highlights the social media and online shopping links. Some larger images slow down loading speed, according to PageSpeed Insights, leading to an overall performance score of 74/100.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="katrina-swanson-fine-art" class="entry-website-title">Katrina Swanson Fine Art</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-katrinamethotswanson-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-katrinamethotswanson-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-katrinamethotswanson-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Katrina Swanson Fine Art"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.katrinamethotswanson.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.katrinamethotswanson.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Omaha, Nebraska, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Katrina Swanson's fine art niche of vintage candy is immediately highlighted in the banner image, which, while it looks like a stock image, is an example of one of her oil paintings. The gallery includes various categories for viewers to browse through, but there is no option to buy online.</p><p>Visitors to the site can view the artist's past events, sign up for an email newsletter, and view other sites where Katrina's artwork is available for sale. While the images shine, the text used is very small.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site features a clean design, simple UX, and high-quality photos of the paintings. An archive of past events and a newsletter to keep up-to-date with future events is a great addition to this artist's site.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>There is no online purchase option and the artist bio is a long block of small text, which hinders legibility. The site is not compliant with assistive technology and all the "Read More" links create an unnecessary amount of clicking and navigation on the site.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-katrinamethotswanson-20240522-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-katrinamethotswanson-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop site uses a clean, simple design to really showcase the artwork and continue the "fine art" theme. The off-white background highlights the images, but the contrast with the text is a bit weaker. The text is also very small and may be difficult for some people to read.</p><p>While there is no option to purchase the art online, this is a great portfolio of the artist's work, and there are plenty of opportunities provided to follow the artist's journey, including social media links and a newsletter.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-katrinamethotswanson-20240522-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-katrinamethotswanson-20240522-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile site is well optimized for the smaller screen, with the small text actually fitting this style and not appearing too small. The colors are bright and vibrant against the off-white background, but the artist's bio still seems a bit overwhelming in the density of the text. The mobile site has a performance score of 64/100 on Google's PageSpeed Insights report.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="the-art-of-marlena-myles" class="entry-website-title">The Art of Marlena Myles</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-marlenamyles-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-marlenamyles-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-marlenamyles-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website The Art of Marlena Myles"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://marlenamyl.es/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://marlenamyl.es/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>St. Paul, Minnesota, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>This site advertises Marlena Myles' work in illustration, animation, fabric design, and public murals inspired by the artist's Native American Dakota heritage. Visitors to the site can download coloring pages that share Dakota culture, read articles and interviews about the artist's work, and buy prints. There is also a link to the artist's fashion designs on Society6.</p><p>A list of future events and links to news articles make for a nice touch on the site, but the site is very busy, which can distract from navigation, and would benefit from customer reviews.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is easy to navigate and full of information, the images clearly show the artist's work, and there is a list of awards to inspire confidence. The links to news articles also work to build confidence in the artist and client trust.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is overpopulated with text blocks, so visitors must scroll and search to find the information they need. The site is only semi-compliant with assistive technologies, and WAVE reports a number of missing alternative text and empty heading errors.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-marlenamyles-20240522-desktop.webp"
