class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile site is well optimized for the smaller screen but has had to make some adjustments, such as leaving out the heading for each of the groups under the "Collections" tab. The about-the-artist page, which includes a bio, statement, and resume, is dense and long on the smaller screen. The mobile site has a performance score of 45/100 on Google's PageSpeed Insights report.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="avery-o-design" class="entry-website-title">Avery O Design</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-averyodesign-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-averyodesign-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-averyodesign-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Avery O Design"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.averyodesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.averyodesign.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Austin, Texas, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>The Avery O Design website advertises hand-painted wall murals, illustrations, and graphic art. It has a fun, casual aesthetic with bright colors, a handwritten typeface, and a funky picture of the artist.</p><p>Visitors to the site will enjoy the blog and social media links, while the various art styles are well organized for easy navigation and the detailed contact form helps with commissioning the artist. The addition of customer testimonials helps to build confidence in the artist.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>WAVE reports less than five missing text and contrast errors on the site. The bright colors and handwritten typeface enhance the artist's style and the fun images of the artist create a personal bond with the visitor.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is only semi-compliant with assistive technologies and lacks an online purchasing option, a list of past and future events, and guidelines on the commissioning process.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-averyodesign-20240522-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-averyodesign-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The grid layout within the gallery keeps the design clean and well-structured, helping with the user experience, and the addition of customer reviews helps to build trust. The addition of a blog seems to be a common theme on artist websites, but the personal, chatty tone of this blog creates a connection between the artist and the reader. On Google's PageSpeed Insights report, the desktop site has a performance rating of 73/100.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-averyodesign-20240522-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-averyodesign-20240522-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile site is well optimized to fit the smaller screen, with no text or images appearing to be cut off in any way. The gallery images can be enlarged by clicking on them and the menu is consistently at the top of each page, with only the home page featuring a back-to-top button. The mobile site has a performance score of 37/100 on Google's PageSpeed Insights report.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
class="entry-container entry-container-content"><div
class="entry-content-wrapper"><div
class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="nola-muller" class="entry-website-title">Nola Muller</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-nolamuller-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-nolamuller-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-nolamuller-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website Nola Muller"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://nolamuller.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://nolamuller.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>Cape Town, Western Cape, South Africa</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>The Nola Muller website showcases this artist's works in oils, acrylics, and watercolors. The website is clean and very straightforward, featuring no extra pages, so the addition of a menu with "Home" as the only tab is redundant. The site is a simple gallery of the artist's work with a list of past exhibitions, a contact form, and social media links. The color palette is warm and earthy, referencing the nature themes of the art.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is simple with high-quality images and only a handful of contrast errors and missing form labels reported on WAVE. The earthy color palette of the site really highlights the artist's influences.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is not compliant with assistive technologies, and lacks any interactive features, client testimonials, descriptions about the artwork, or information about buying works or commissioning the artist.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-nolamuller-20240522-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-nolamuller-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The desktop site makes good use of the larger screen sizes and a clean grid layout to highlight the artworks on display and make a visual impact. However, small text in a lighter color against a pastel background creates poor contrast and legibility. Due to the limited scope, the site loads quickly, leading to a performance score of 83/100 on PageSpeed Insights.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-nolamuller-20240522-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-nolamuller-20240522-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile site is functional, with the responsive design ensuring that images and text blocks scale appropriately to the smaller screen sizes. However, the images of the artwork lose some visual impact due to the smaller sizes.</p><p>The mobile site has a more yellow-toned color palette, compared to the desktop site's more pink-toned colors, leading to a better contrast between the text and background. PageSpeed Insights awards the mobile site a performance score of 88/100.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
