class="section-faq"><div
class="container"><h2 id=fAQs class="section-heading">FAQs:</h2><div
class="row"><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-kind-of-website-should-an-artist-have class="question">What kind of website should an artist have?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>An artist's website typically features clean white backgrounds and a gallery of images that shine against the stark white. The site should also include an artist's statement and bio, and a way to contact the artist to commission work. Depending on the site, some artists may include online purchasing of their work.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-does-an-artist-website-look-like class="question">What does an artist website look like?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>An artist's website typically features white backgrounds with images of the artist's work, inspired by how galleries display artwork.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=do-artists-still-need-a-website class="question">Do artists still need a website?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Yes, in our increasingly online world, artists need to promote and share their work online in order to build a customer base and start selling their work.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=what-are-some-famous-artist-website-examples class="question">What are some famous artist website examples?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>We've compiled a list of artist websites and have discussed the areas that work well, design-wise.</p></div></div><div
class="col-12 faq-item"><h3 id=where-can-i-find-the-top-10-artist-websites class="question">Where can I find the top 10 artist websites?</h3><div
class="answer"><p>Take a look at our <a
href="#rose-hewartson">9 examples for some great artist websites</a> and how to learn from them.</p></div></div><div
